{Another very good example of the strenght of the advance f2-f4. After f2-f4,
White's attack develops easily.} 15. Nf5 ({White can also start with} 15. f4 {
, and after} exf4 16. Rxf4 Kh8 17. Rcf1 f6 18. Nf5 Qf8 19. h4 $1 {continue
with the same attacking pattern.}) 15... Qf6 (15... Qf8 {is not any better.}
16. f4 Re6 $5 (16... exf4 17. Qxf4 Rac8 (17... Ne5 18. d4 Ng6 19. Qxc7) 18.
Nh6+ gxh6 19. Qg4+) 17. fxe5 Nxe5 18. d4 Ng6 19. Qxc7 Rxe4 20. Qxb7 Nf4 21. Ng3
