Qg5 22. Qf2 Nc8 23. Nf5 $1 Re8 ({Black should carefully arrange his pieces, as
there are many hidden tricks like} 23... Nd6 $2 24. Nxg7 $1 $18) 24. Rf1 Nd6
25. h4 {White has a pleasant choice.} (25. Nxg7 $5) (25. g4 $5) 25... Qg6 26.
