$16) 22. N3h2 $1 $16 {[%cal Gf2f4,Ge4e5] In preparation for the kingside
attack.} (22. Ng3 Ne7 23. Kg2 Kh8 $14) 22... Qd8 (22... Ne7 23. f4 Kh8 24. f5
$16) 23. f4 exf4 (23... Be7 24. f5 $16) 24. Qxf4 {[%cal Ge4e5] The black
pieces are too far away from the e5 square, thus the break e4-e5 can be only
stopped with the help of the f7-f6 push.} Qe7 25. Nf3 (25. Ng3 $5 Qe5 26. Qf2)
25... f6 {[%csl Re6] This however weakens the kingside as well as the e6 spot.
And, strictly speaking does not stop the break.} 26. Ng3 Rd8 (26... Qf7 27. Rf1
Re7 28. e5 $5 (28. Rf2 Ne8 29. Raf1 $140 $2 g5) (28. Qd2 Ne8 29. Be3 Qg7 30.
Kh2 $16) 28... dxe5 (28... fxe5 29. Qe3 Ne8 (29... Qe8 30. Ne4 Rf7 31. Nfg5
Rxf1+ 32. Rxf1 $18) 30. Bg5 Qg7 31. Bxe7 Qxe7 32. Rf2 $16) 29. Qe3 Ne8 (29...
f5 30. Nxe5 Qe8 31. Rae1 Nd6 32. Qf4 $16) 30. Ne4 Bxh6 31. Qxh6 Ncd6 32. Nxc5
$16) 27. Rf1 Ne8 (27... Ra7 $5) 28. Bxf8 Qxf8 29. e5 $1 $18 dxe5 (29... fxe5
