{[#] This is the dream queenside structure for White. Once the queenside is
locked, White has a free hand on the other wing. There are two possibilities
of building the kingside attack: 1) g2-g4 followed by Nbd2-f1-g3 2) The
advance f2-f4 Due to White's tremendous space advantage, he can easily
transfer his pieces from one wing to another. For example, one can immediately
spot the empty second rank. Very often White manages to bring his a1-rook to
the kingside via the a2-square. Black is strategically lost in such positions.
}  *

