{[%csl Rb5][%cal Gb2b3,Ga2a4,Ga4b5,Ga6b5] [#] The second typical strategy is
to create queenside weaknesses. Mostly this idea is being executed after a2-a4
followed by axb5. As a result, the b5-pawn is getting vulnerable. Afterwards,
White starts putting pressure on the pawn with simple moves such as Bd3 and
Qe2. Before playing a2-a4, White usually starts with b2-b3 in order to prevent
the response ...c5-c4.}  *

