{Very often even the symmetrical positions are not simple. In many cases,
White can create problems for his opponent, due to the space advantage
provided by the d5-pawn. The space advantage, however, should be combined with
a superior piece activity. Of course, things can work the other way round. If
Black has more active pieces, he can even be slightly better.}  *

