{[#] The following example shows that even in a symmetrical pawn structure,
with all queenside pawns being exchanged, White often puts pressure due to his
space advantage. In the position on the diagram, Black played} 14... c4 {
This move is generally reasonable when White has a pawn on a4 or a3. Black's
next move is going to be ...Nc5. Nevertheless, things are not that simple. The
Chinese grandmaster demonstrated a subtle understanding of the structure -} 15.
b3 cxb3 16. Bxb3 {White is planning to prepare the advance c3-c4.} ({After} 16.
Nxb3 Qc7 17. Bd3 Qxc3 18. Be3 Qc7 {Black has a decent position.}) 16... Qc7 17.
Re3 Nc5 18. Ba3 Nfd7 $6 {Unfortunate decision. Black's priority should be the
activation of the light-squared bishop.} ({Better would have been} 18... Reb8
19. c4 Bc8 {When Black is ready for the opening of the queenside.}) 19. c4 $1 {
White immediately goes for the symmetrical pawn structure. He will have a big
advantage due to the extra space and the passivity of the black pieces.} Qa5
20. cxb5 axb5 21. axb5 Qxb5 22. Bc4 {White starts gaining tempose by using the
inferior position of the black queen.} Qb6 23. Rb1 Qc7 24. Bb5 $1 {Remember
that in such structures, the bishop is perfectly placed on the diagonal a4-e8.}
Reb8 25. Qc2 Qd8 26. Rc1 $6 {Not hte most precise continuation.} ({White
should have played} 26. Bxd7 Nxd7 27. Nc4 $16 {[%csl Rb7,Rd6] with a
tremendous pressure.}) 26... Ba6 27. Bc6 Ra7 28. Nc4 Rc8 29. Bb4 Bb7 $2 {
A very important positional mistake.} ({Having less space, Black should have
tried to exchange pieces. Therefore, better would have been} 29... Bxc4 30.
Qxc4 Rb8 31. Kh2 Qb6 32. Rb1 Na6 33. Reb3 Nxb4 34. Rxb4 Qc7 $11 {with equality.
}) 30. Na5 $16 {White has a huge advantage. Later on, Wang Hao converted it
without problems.} Rxa5 31. Bxb7 Rb8 32. Bxa5 Qxa5 33. Bc6 Nf6 34. Ree1 Rb4 35.
Nd2 g6 36. Ra1 Qc7 37. Reb1 Rxb1+ 38. Qxb1 Kg7 39. g3 h5 40. h4 Ng4 41. Ra8 g5
42. hxg5 Bxg5 43. Nc4 h4 44. gxh4 Bxh4 45. f3 Nh6 46. Re8 Qa7 47. Kh1 Kh7 48.
Bb5 Nb3 49. Qxb3 Qf2 50. Qe3 Qf1+ 51. Kh2 Ng4+ 52. fxg4 1-0

