{Despite the fact that Black had established a solid blockade on d5, White's
kingside initiative looks dangerous. How to continue? White to move} 25. Rf6 $1
{Very subtle move. White not only prevents his opponent from playing f7-f6
pawn but at the same time, he puts pressure on the weak d6-pawn. A possible
idea is to exchange the queens by means of Qf4 after which the d6-pawn will be
lost.} Re7 {Black protects the f7-pawn and intends to play Ne8. Nevertheless,
his last move is a tactical mistake. How to make use of it?} 26. Nf5+ $1 {
Very energetic solution. It turns out that at the end, the e7-rook will be
hanging.} Bxf5 27. R6xf5 gxf5 28. Rxf5 {White is winning since Black has no
way to protect the e7-rook.} *

