{[#]} 19. g4 $5 {This move shows White's intention to go for a typical
exchange sacrifice.} ({More traditional would have been} 19. Bh6 Ng7 20. g4 {
[%cal Gf1g3]}) 19... Nf4 20. Bxf4 exf4 21. Qd2 Bf6 22. Qxf4 $1 Bxa1 23. Rxa1 f6
24. Ng3 {White has a tremendous compensation for the exchange. Actually, Black
cannot activate his rooks. At the same time, White will keep developing his
kingside initiative.} Ne7 25. Qh6 Rf7 {At this point, White should have played}
26. e5 $1 ({The game Caruana - Naroditsky, 2020 followed} 26. Kg2 Qd8 27. Nh4
Qf8 28. Qxf8+ Rfxf8 29. f4 g5 30. Nhf5 Ng6 31. Nxd6 Nxf4+ 32. Kf3 Rad8 33. Nb7
