{[#]} 1. Nc3 $1 {Remember this typical structure. Even though the c4-pawn is a
protected passed pawn, it's not going anywhere. White can also easily protect
the a3-pawn. He has two positional ideas in this structure - kingside attack
and the advance a3-a4 played under favourable circumstances.} *

