Ba6 20. Bxa6 Rxa6 {with pressure along the a-file.}) (18. Bxb4 $2 exd4 {
leaves White in an inferior position since Black has control over the centre.})
18... Rb8 $1 {This is better to keep the Qd8 to play ...d6-d5} (18... Qb8 $1 {
In this way, Black manages to maintain the material balance.} 19. Bxb4 Bxd5 20.
Bc3 (20. Bd2 Bb7 21. a4 d5 22. b4 c5 23. b5) 20... Bb7 {Black had a
