Bxd5 20. Bd2 (20. Bc3 Ba8) 20... Ba8 21. a4 d5) ({In case of} 16. d5 c6 17. c4
{a6-a5 also turns out to be a vital move. After} a4 $1 (17... Nc5 18. Be3 bxc4
19. bxc4 Nfd7 20. Qd2 (20. h4) 20... Qc7 {, Black is in time to regroup his
pieces and start attacking the c4-pawn. Kiran,M - Mohota,N Kolkata 2013}) 18.
cxb5 (18. dxc6 Bxc6 19. cxb5 Bxb5 20. bxa4 Bc6) 18... cxd5 19. bxa4 dxe4 20.
Nxe4 Bxe4 21. Bxe4 Nxe4 22. Rxe4 Nc5) ({Harmless is also} 16. Bd3 b4 17. cxb4
