30,8,25,32,41,31,34,25,44,9,-4,17,17,20,21,30,22,27,8,-13,9,-29,-9,-9,0,-14,
-22]} 1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Bb5 a6 4. Ba4 Nf6 5. O-O Be7 6. Re1 b5 7. Bb3 d6
8. c3 O-O 9. h3 Nb8 10. d4 Nbd7 11. Nbd2 Bb7 12. Bc2 Re8 13. Nf1 Bf8 14. Ng3 g6
15. a4 {This is by far the most common move in the position. By attacking the
b5 White is trying to provoke c7-c6, which would release the pressure on the
